# Golden corpora are byte-exact baselines: a procedural/determinism golden is
# only meaningful if it round-trips byte-for-byte. Mark every committed golden
# blob as binary so git never applies line-ending (LF<->CRLF) or other text
# normalization to it, on any platform. Without this, a golden that happens to
# contain no NUL byte could be silently CRLF-converted on a Windows checkout and
# no longer match the bytes a generator produces.
*.bin binary

# Golden corpus directories (any extension) are stored verbatim. A golden dir may
# sit directly under `tests/` (`tests/golden/`) or be namespaced under a subdir
# (e.g. a game's `tests/retro_fps/golden/`), so match a `golden/` dir at any depth.
**/tests/golden/** binary
**/tests/**/golden/** binary
